Saddened by the news of the loss of legendary actor Alan Arkin. I absolutely loved his work. Such a creative force! It was one of the great privileges of my life to get to film Alan for our documentary "Sr." Arkin loved Downey Sr and they were great friends. May their spirits soar together on the other side 🕊️♥️ Photo: @emibarc #alanarkin

Excited to share news about a doc project I've been producing "The Jewel" with @prairiesurfcreative  which highlights efforts to save the historic Jewel Theater, Oklahoma City's oldest African-American owned theater. I was also brought in to help shoot scenes and do some initial editing, alongside an incredible team. Check out the OFFICIAL TRAILER (Link in Bio) 📸: Matt Hode @_theoklahoman

@stplegacy recently restored footage shot by @carterbsmith & I of a legendary night with @stpband at Irving Place, NYC in early 2000. (link in bio)
 
It was an emotional night as it was singer Scott Weiland's first show after being released from prison. The crowd was full of love. Seeing the video brings back so many memories, especially how much fun Carter & I had immersing in the world of Rock n' Roll back then. Seeing @scottweiland here is also a painful reminder to me of how strong the current of addiction is, and how devastating it can be for so many. Still, overall, the video conjures a feeling of warmth for an era that is now long gone.

@bronxdocumentarycenter launched a new exhibition last night of the work of renowned photographer Sylvia Plachy. @sylviaplachy has been a photographer all her life, and for 30 years she was on staff with @villagevoice covering NYC. Her family and friends were on hand to celebrate the exhibition which will run through 11/5/24 at BDC. Check it out if you are in the area. Such incredibly soulful work.
Don Piper & Laura Poe, marriage party 9/30/23 NYC

At the Mount Wilson Observatory over 100 years ago Edwin Hubble discovered that our universe was expanding. It was especially meaningful to me to have the opportunity to visit this historic place with my old friend @stephenperkinsdrummer on our never-ending adventure, In Search of Rhythm, and meditate about the bigger picture - our place in this expanding universe. Thank you to Jessica Rodriguez at Mount Wilson Observatory for sharing so much knowledge with us on our visit. Please consider visiting @mtwilsonobservatory near Pasadena and prepare to have your mind opened wide.

@emibarc & I are so thankful to the jury @griersontrust British Documentary Awards for the incredible honor of selecting our film "Sr." as Best Arts Documentary -- and I am eternally grateful for the genius of #robertdowneysr & also grateful to his son @robertdowneyjr for making it all happen. 🕊️🎬❤️ #griersonawards

Today we mourn the loss of Norman Lear, a wonderful artist and person who inspired us greatly and loved his old friend Downey Sr. Emily and I had the great privilege to hang out with Mr. Lear during the making of our doc "Sr." Each time was a life memory that we will always cherish. He radiated creativity and coolness. Cheers to his life and example! May his spirit soar on the other side!
